## Step 5: How they work best (the "How I'm like" section)

> **Q5. How do you work and think best?**

**5a. Working style:**
> A) I prefer deep focus on a few things at a time
> B) I like variety — I do better with multiple threads running in parallel
> C) I need structure and deadlines to produce; I don't self-direct easily
> D) I do my best work autonomously with a clear goal but no prescribed method

**5b. Environment:**
> A) I thrive in small, high-autonomy environments (startups, freelance, solo work)
> B) I do well in larger organizations if I have clear scope
> C) I'm not sure yet — I haven't had enough variety to know

**5c. What kind of work energizes you? (pick up to 2)**
> A) Figuring out why people do what they do (psychology, behavior, motivation)
> B) Building things (products, systems, tools, creative work)
> C) Strategy and decision-making (figuring out what to do and why)
> D) Communicating and translating (making complex things clear)
> E) Researching and synthesizing (understanding things deeply before acting)
> F) Optimizing and improving (finding inefficiencies and fixing them)
> G) Other: ____________

**5d. (Scaffolded/guided mode only)** What's the gap between how you work now and how you want to work?
> A) I have the skills but not the environment
> B) I have the environment but haven't developed the skills
> C) Both need work
> D) I'm mostly there

Store these answers. They become the "How I'm like" section — used by the AI to frame career and intellectual recommendations.

In `deep` mode, add one follow-up:
> "What's one environment where you did your best work, and one where you felt drained? Why?"

