## Step 7: 1-year goals (per pillar)

> **Q7. What would a genuine win look like in 1 year for each of your pillars?**

*Ask about the anchor pillar first, then the others. Use their calibration level to determine how open-ended the prompts are.*

**For each pillar:**

**Career (if anchor):**
> A) I have a specific job / company / role type I'm aiming for → describe it
> B) I'm figuring out what role type fits me best → "clarity on role type + at least one strong interview process"
> C) I want to grow within my current role → "promoted / expanded scope / specific new skill"
> D) I want to build something of my own → describe the milestone

**Fitness:**
> A) Visual goal (specific body composition change, fits into a specific item of clothing)
> B) Performance goal (lift X, run Y, sport milestone)
> C) Habit goal (gym Nx/week as reliable default)
> D) All of the above — let them describe

**Social:**
> A) I have 2–3 communities I attend regularly
> B) I have a group of 5–8 people I actually want to spend time with
> C) I'm not anxious to initiate anymore — it's just what I do
> D) Their own: ____________

**Intellectual:**
> A) I've shipped 3–6 projects (started + ended + output + >1 week each)
> B) I've built a consistent output habit — not just bursts
> C) I've completed one specific project that matters to me → name it
> D) I've built a public presence or reputation in something

If `deep` mode, force success criteria for each selected pillar:
> "How will we know this is achieved — what specific evidence would prove it?"

