## Step 10: Next steps

After generating the file, say:

> "Your Life Arc is set. Here's what to do next:
>
> 1. **Read it** — does it sound like you? If anything feels off, tell me and we'll fix it.
> 2. **First weekly check-in:** Type `weekly check-in` next Tuesday. The AI will load your Life Arc automatically — you won't need to re-explain anything.
> 3. **Monthly reset:** At the end of this month (or whenever you're ready to set your first monthly targets), type `monthly reset`.
>
> One thing to know: the system gets better over time. The first month is rough calibration. By month 3, it knows your patterns well enough to push back on you."

Then run this checklist before ending:
- Confirm `Life-Arc-Overview.md` exists in repo root
- Confirm weekly command works: user can type `weekly check-in`
- Confirm monthly command works: user can type `monthly reset`
- Confirm personal-data files are ignored by Git
- If user chose Notion "now", confirm MCP test passed

